        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens shared web provider registry mapping: web search/fetch provider rows are read through bounded registry-entry access before scope filtering so one unreadable provider row does not hide healthy providers\n- rebased over current `origin/main`, resolving the Responses image payload sanitizer conflict by keeping the shared inline-image sanitizer plus the branch's circular/unreadable/non-JSON protections\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `9327a799343602bca871284d6f98f375e60fe1d3`, proven on `origin/main` at `b09cab4ebd2c8279e7ddb8987f7ac105008b4268`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/plugins/web-provider-resolution-shared.ts src/plugins/web-provider-resolution-candidates.test.ts src/agents/responses-image-payload-sanitizer.ts src/agents/responses-image-payload-sanitizer.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main..HEAD`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/plugins/web-provider-resolution-shared.ts src/plugins/web-provider-resolution-candidates.test.ts src/agents/responses-image-payload-sanitizer.ts src/agents/responses-image-payload-sanitizer.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/web-provider-resolution-candidates.test.ts src/agents/responses-image-payload-sanitizer.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 2 files passed, 17 tests passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean before commit on the web-provider mapping slice\n- scrubbed touched files/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, memory embedding provider registration, runtime embedding adapter merge/direct lookup, process-global embedding provider registry restore/list/register paths, migration provider runtime resolution, provider contract registry resolution, setup-only provider/backend runtime registration, compaction provider registration, capability provider runtime resolution, provider runtime hook lookup, shared provider resolver projection, active runtime CLI backend projection, provider discovery entry projection, explicit web provider public artifact projection, document/web-content extractor public artifact projection, trusted tool policy decision handling, Gateway Control UI descriptor projection, Gateway plugin session action dispatch, dynamic plugin session action method-scope resolution, plugin-registered Gateway method descriptor scope resolution, channel plugin Gateway method discovery, `tools.catalog` active registry metadata projection, plugin inspect/status Gateway method summaries, plugin inspect/status registry-entry summaries, plugin inspect/status plugin-record projection, effective tool inventory metadata projection, lightweight channel registry lookup/channel id normalization, loaded channel plugin resolution/conversation lookup, loaded channel read-helper lookup, outbound active-registry channel fallback, outbound channel bootstrap gating, channel plugin registry loaders, auto-reply channel default-account resolution, generic current-conversation binding support detection, plugin command conversation binding resolution, heartbeat channel plugin resolution, scoped channel setup snapshot resolution, plugin registry channel registration duplicate checks, plugin registry provider duplicate checks, runtime synthetic/external auth ref discovery, model catalog registration dedupe, runtime registry configured-channel reuse, provider install catalog projection, and shared web provider registry mapping no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable labels/auth fields, unreadable backend configs, unreadable CLI commands, hostile callback metadata, throwing provider/extractor factories, unreadable public artifact metadata, throwing trusted policy evaluators, unreadable trusted policy decision fields, unreadable gateway descriptor metadata, unreadable session action metadata, malformed matched action scopes, unreadable gateway method descriptor names/scopes, unreadable channel gateway method arrays/elements, unreadable tool metadata entries, unreadable tool metadata records, unreadable deferred tool entries, unreadable deferred tool ownership fields, unreadable inspect Gateway method descriptor owners/names, unreadable inspect typed hook/custom hook/tool/diagnostic/memory-provider registry fields, unreadable inspect plugin-record ids/kinds/summary arrays/metadata, unreadable effective-inventory tool metadata rows, unreadable channel registry entries, unreadable channel plugin ids, unreadable channel alias metadata, unreadable loaded channel plugin records, unreadable loaded channel order metadata, unreadable read-path loaded channel records, unreadable outbound active registry channel entries, unreadable outbound fallback plugin ids, unreadable bootstrap channel entries, unreadable bootstrap plugin ids, unreadable bootstrap send-capability fields, unreadable channel loader entries, unreadable channel loader plugin ids, throwing channel loader callbacks, unreadable channel default-account registry entries, unreadable current-conversation channel entries, unreadable current-conversation alias metadata, unreadable command-binding channel entries, unreadable heartbeat channel entries, unreadable setup snapshot entries, unreadable existing channel registration entries, unreadable existing provider registration entries, unreadable synthetic auth refs, unreadable external auth refs, unreadable synthetic/external auth provider/backend ids, unreadable existing model catalog provider ids, unreadable model catalog owner plugin ids, unreadable model catalog kinds, unreadable active channel registry entries, unreadable provider-index plugin/install/auth-choice metadata, or unreadable web provider registry rows while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, based on `origin/main` at `b09cab4ebd2c8279e7ddb8987f7ac105008b4268`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: after the shared web provider registry mapping slice and the rebase conflict resolution, ran focused formatting, branch diff check, linting, Vitest, synthetic/private-name scrub, and autoreview commands listed in Verification.\n\nEvidence after fix: `web-provider-resolution-candidates.test.ts` seeds an unreadable `fuzzplugin` web provider registry row and proves the scoped healthy `mockplugin` provider remains visible. `responses-image-payload-sanitizer.test.ts` also passed after the rebase conflict resolution.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed web provider registry rows no longer abort web search/fetch provider resolution before healthy rows are copied; the Responses image payload sanitizer keeps both shared inline-image canonicalization and circular/unreadable payload handling after rebasing.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate and AWS Crabbox broad gate were not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted shared web provider registry mapping surface, the sanitizer conflict test, and formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
